reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, affordable and practical
reviews.reviewText: These guys are great for our work vehicles. I in fact, have some in my personal vehicle as well. The first aid kits are small, and easily tucked away under receipt or in the back of a trunk. These are no-brainer as whether you need it or someone else needs it this kit can always be handy. It is not intended for, any advanced medical aid, but it does provide for your basic needs. For my Window Cleaning team, there are many times where we scrape our hand against something or cut it against our window scraper blades that we use. The first kit makes it possible for us to continue doing the job without having to stop and go to a doctors office or to a pharmacy.

reviews.reviewText: I could not for the life of me figure out how to open this thing when my finger was bleeding! I almost got injured again just trying to figure it out. I wound up ripping the blue plastic knobs things right off just so I could get to a band aid and now it wont close so I have to use a rubber band to hold it closed because it doesn't close on its own now. Absolutely ridiculous storage with no directions on how to open it. Its a hard pass.
